I had high hopes for this recipe and was sadly disappointed. I would be giving 2.5 forks if possible...I'm used to Indian food having such exciting flavors that this paled in comparison to just about every other Indian dish I've made/ordered. I made exactly as the recipe stated but I should have listened to the other reviewers and doubled the spices because it turned out so bland despite looking so fabulous. It has potential so I will be making again with a few changes: 1) Nuke the potatoes for a few minutes before roasting so they finish at the same time as the cauliflower (or omit them all together), 2) Double the spices...maybe add the first half as directed and the second half when I add the roast veggies to the onion mixture, 3) I added peas to the final few minutes to add a pop of color and they were a great addition; will keep those next time. Hopefully the next round will be better.

