Rating: 3
This is one of my favorite Indian side dishes. I love the caramelized flavors that roasting the veggies brings. I do agree with some reviewers that the level of spice is too timid. I double all of the spices and the garlic, ginger and jalapeno as well. Even with that the spice level is less than what you would find with this same dish in an Indian restaurant. I disagree with the instructions to cook the garlic, ginger and jalapeno with the onions 8 to 10 min. The garlic gets too bitter and browns much faster than the onion. I like to cook the onions in the oil until they are starting to get golden and then I add the garlic, ginger and jalapeno for the last 2-3 minutes. I also like to add some peas before covering and cooking the last 5 minutes.

