Rating: 3
This dish is really quite wonderful. I've roasted practically every other vegetable before, but hadn't tried roasting cauliflower since I've never been a huge fan. Like brussels sprouts, raosting changes the nature of this vegetable completely, bringing out a delicate nuttiness and sweetness that you'd never guess is there. The only change I made was cutting back on the cayenne slightly, and using more cauliflower, but no potatoes, just b/c I wanted to see what the cauliflower was like just by itself. My friend Julie who is Indian says this is authentically Indian, but not Southern Indian.

